1:
Awake, awake, put on your strength, Zion;
\q1 put on your beautiful garments, Jerusalem, holy city;
\q1 for never again will the uncircumcised or the unclean enter you.

2:
Shake yourself off from the dust; arise and sit, Jerusalem;
\q1 take off the chain from your neck, captive, daughter of Zion.
\q1

9:
Break out into joyful singing together, you ruins of Jerusalem;
\q1 for Yahweh has comforted his people; he has redeemed Jerusalem.
\q1

11:
Leave, leave, go out from there; touch nothing unclean;
\q1 leave from her midst; purify yourselves, you who carry the vessels of Yahweh.
\q1

13:
Look, my servant will act wisely;
\q1 he will be high and lifted up, and he will be exalted.
\q1
